emuInput.TitMainTitle: Group of young men and young women seated on folding chairs at banquet tables during Youth Lyceum banquet in Warren Methodist Church
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1957, pg. A8 reads: "Youth Lyceum Meets - Upper photo: Atty. Byrd Brown, standing, gave an inspiring address on the duty of teen-agers to themselves and the community, at the Youth Lyceum banquet, held in Warren Methodist Church, Saturday evening. Other guests included, left to right, Jack Butler, who introduced the guest speaker; Clair Coogan, vice principal at Schenley High School; Miss Gwendolyn L. Poinsetta, Attorney Brown, Carolyn Dickerson, Regis Bobonis and Beverly J. Butler...-Harris Photo."
